    "problemStatement": "Chef has a knapsack with a volume capacity of VVV.\n\nThere are NNN items where the ithi^{th}ith item has volume XiX_iXi\u200b and value YiY_iYi\u200b (Xi\u22c5Yi\u2264109)(X_i\\cdot Y_i \\leq 10^9)(Xi\u200b\u22c5Yi\u200b\u2264109).\n\nNote that each item can be selected **at most once**.\n\nFind the **maximum value** Chef can get without exceeding the volume capacity of knapsack.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of input will contain a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases.\nEach test case consists of multiple lines of input.\n\nThe first line of each test case contains two space-separated integers NNN and VVV \u2014 the number of items and the volume capacity of knapsack.\nThe next NNN lines describe the items. The ithi^{th}ith of these NNN lines contains two space-separated integers XiX_iXi\u200b and YiY_iYi\u200b, denoting the volume and value respectively.\n\n\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output on a new line, the maximum value Chef can get without exceeding the capacity of knapsack.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22641001 \\leq T \\leq 1001\u2264T\u2264100",
      "1\u2264N\u22641001 \\leq N \\leq 1001\u2264N\u2264100",
      "1\u2264V,Xi,Yi\u22641091 \\leq V,X_i,Y_i \\leq 10^91\u2264V,Xi\u200b,Yi\u200b\u2264109",
      "1\u2264Xi\u22c5Yi\u22641091 \\leq X_i\\cdot Y_i \\leq 10^91\u2264Xi\u200b\u22c5Yi\u200b\u2264109",
      "The sum of NNN over all test cases won't exceed 100100100."
    ],
